member.remarks:
This attribute is the storage-layer equivalent of the provider-layer DataSourceAttribute (ADR-005), enabling the same plugin discovery pattern for storage backends.
Once discovered, a sink can be activated via the Storage.Sinks configuration list without any code changes to the composition root:
"Storage": { "Sinks": ["jsonl", "parquet", "clickhouse"] }

example.code:
[StorageSink("clickhouse", "ClickHouse Storage")]
public sealed class ClickHouseSink : IStorageSink
{
    // Implementation
}

member.remarks:
Mirrors the DataSourceRegistry pattern from the provider layer (ADR-005).
Usage in the composition root:

var registry = new StorageSinkRegistry();
registry.DiscoverFromAssemblies(typeof(JsonlStorageSink).Assembly);
// registry.Sinks now contains JsonlStorageSink, ParquetStorageSink, etc.
